South Atlantic Financial Corpsaid it has agreed in principle to merge with IndependenceHolding Co into a new company to be called SAFCO InternationalLtd.    It said each South Atlantic share would be exchanged forone SAFCO share and each Independence share for 2.822 SAFCOshares.    Independence now owns about 40 pct of South Atlantic's 9.8mln primary common shares.    South Atlantic said said its chairman and chief executiveofficer Sheldon S. Gordon would have the same posts with SAFCOand Independence president Ronald G. Strackbein would bepresident of SAFCO.    The company said the transaction is subject to execution ofdefinitive agreements, the receipt of fairness opinions frominvestment banks and approval by boards and shareholders ofboth companies.  It said proxy materials are expected to bemaioled this quarter.   Both South Atlantic and Independenceare insurance companies. Reuter&#3;